text:
Stream #13 Florida @ #11 Kentucky Now Stream Live Zion Williamson kisses rim with windmill dunk in title game Zion Williamson dunk in today's SCISA AA championship game - #SDSGriffins @ZionW32 pic.twitter.com/S8J9WomIYW — Middlemarch (@latoo2) February 25, 2017 We — Middlemarch (@latoo2) February 25, 2017 
We haven't seen a leaper like five-star titan Zion Williamson , the No. 2 player in the 2018 class per the 247Sports Composite, since LeBron James . 
The 6-foot-7, 230-pound forward from Spartanburg, S.C., finished his junior season averaging 36.9 points per game and capped it off with another jaw-dropping outing — highlighted by a monster windmill dunk — in Saturday's 76-51 state championship game victory over Christian Academy. 
This jam from teammate Chandler Lindsey wasn't bad either.
